This paper discusses the concept of dependency distance minimization (DDm) in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces a graph theoretic approach to analyze the syntactic dependency structures, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper uses statistical tests to verify the hypothesis, which could be categorized under statistics (cs.SI).
